descript.abstract: FEMA flood prone areas with 100 foot buffer. Original flood prone areas where table digitized into the City of Seattle GIS CGDB control layer in the mid 90's. The 100 buffer was added in 2007 in order to prevent flood prone area ommisions during initial site observations and plan review. Layer may be used without the buffer by unselecting or defining out the flood = 1 feature type.
descript.purpose: This layer is used by the City as an aid to evaluate construction sites for the presence of flood prone areas pertinent to Environmentally Critical Areas regulations.
